      "sections": [
        {
          "type": "intro",
          "text": "Introduction\nAlphabet Test questions are based on the positions and arrangements of\nletters in the English alphabet series. They test a child’s ability to:\ny Recognise letter positions (forward & backward order).\ny Rearrange letters to form meaningful words.\ny Identify patterns and skipped letters.\ny Pick the correct options based on the given clues.\nTypes of Alphabet Test\nType I: Arrange letters to form a meaningful word\nUse the given numbers (representing letters) to rearrange into\na meaningful word.\nExample 1: Form a meaningful word by arranging the given numbers corre-\nsponding to the letters below.\nLetter S E T B\nNumber 1 2 3 4\n(A) 4, 1, 3, 2 (B) 4, 2, 1, 3 (C) 4, 3, 2, 1 (D) 2, 4, 1, 3\nAnswer: (B) BEST\nType II: Word formation from given letters\nCheck if an option word can or cannot be formed from the given letters.\nExample 2: Which word cannot be formed from letters of word MOTHER?\n(A) OTHER (B) MORE (C) THEM (D) TOWER\nAnswer: (D) TOWER\n\nType III: Form a meaningful word from jumbled letters\nArrange the given jumbled letters to form a real word.\nExample 3: Form a meaningful word by arranging the given numbers corre-\nsponding to the letters below.\nJumbled letters: E T A B L\nCorrect word = T A B L E\nAnswer: TABLE\nType IV: Identify skipped-letter patterns\nFind the options where letters follow the same number of skips as the given\nletter sequence.\nExample 4: Check the sequence.\nACEG\nIn which of the following sequences, the number of letters skipped between\ntwo adjacent letters is the same as the given sequence?\n(A) PQRS (B) MPRU (C) HJLN (D) OMKI\nSolution: In given Sequence ACEG, each letter skips 1 letter (B, D, F).\nSo the pattern is to skip by 1.\nSequence HJLN also follows same rule.\nAnswer: (C) HJLN",
          "questions": []
        },
